   <title><![CDATA[Law and Cosmology: How Do You Answer, ‘Says who?” [God, Law, and Liberty]]]></title>
   <link>https://app.dropwave.io/episode/5e4a33e5-1bbf-464a-ac74-bd23e19431fe/law-and-cosmology-how-do-you-answer-says-who.mp3</link>
   <description><![CDATA[<p>Today David begins to take listeners through the question Yale law professor asked in 1971&mdash;on what basis can we have an authoritative legal system that can answer the equivalent of &ldquo;sez who?&rdquo; question of the playground bully. You will be surprised by Leff&rsquo;s answer. Law professor Philip Johnson called it &ldquo;the modernist impasse.&rdquo; It is a guide to understanding what is going on in American law and the trouble law faces.</p>]]></description>
